<p style="margin: 0px;">Paying for eligible expenses with pre-tax dollars helps to lower the costs of health and dependent care.</p>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;"><span class="body2">Types of reimbursement accounts</span></p>
<ul>
	<li><b>Health care.</b> Designed to pay those expenses not covered under your medical plan and lower your taxable income. You specify a pre-tax deduction. Associates who take advantage of the Health Care Reimbursement Account automatically receive a Bank of America Health Care Card, a debit card that is used to pay for out-of-pocket costs.</li>
	<li><b>Dependent care.</b> Designed to cover anticipated dependent care expenses and lower your taxable income. You specify a pre-tax deduction. You can also use your Bank of America Health Care Card to pay for out-of-pocket costs for dependent care.</li>
</ul>
